Detailed Description

Implementation of TERMINAL INPUT behaviour and BASH HISTORY.

Using termios data structure and library functions we override the behaviour of the default bash/shell to get a non-blocking input behaviour and maintain a buffer ourselves. When enter is pressed we run the command store in the buffer.

History is also store in a dynamically allocated 2D character array. Whenever the history table fills up this array is reallocated.

Author:
Bishal Santra
